dc_title_s: South America, Peru, approach to Paita (Raster Image)
dc_description_s: Prepared and published by the Defense Mapping Agency. Depths shown by isolines and soundings. Relief shown by contours, hachures, and spot heights. "From Peruvian charts to 1980." "Copyright 1996 by the United States Government. No copyright claimed under Title 17 U.S.C." "Soundings in meters." Components: [Approaches] -- Paita. Scale 1:14,991. Includes compilation diagram. Map no.22124 This map is part of a collection of scanned and georeferenced nautical charts produced by the National Geospatial-Intelligence Agency (NGA). United States. Defense Mapping Agency. (1996). South America, Peru, approach to Paita (Raster Image). LandInfo. Available at: https://purl.stanford.edu/zr996xy1641 This layer is presented in the WGS84 coordinate system for web display purposes. Downloadable data are provided in native coordinate system or projection.
